                <h1>Discover the Origin of Whataburger: A Texas Tradition</h1>
                <p>Whataburger originated in Corpus Christi, Texas, where it was founded by Harmon Dobson in 1950. The restaurant quickly gained popularity for its large, juicy burgers and unique flavor, leading to its expansion throughout Texas and beyond. Today, Whataburger is a beloved fast-food chain known for its signature orange-and-white striped A-frame buildings.</p>
